in conversation with bill drayton events at stanford in conversation with bill drayton facebook twitter email print add to calendar join stanford graduate school of business professor bill meehan for a dialogue with legendary changemaker bill drayton ashoka ceo founder and macarthur fellow drayton envisions a world that responds quickly and effectively to social challenges and where each individual has the freedom confidence and societal support to address any social problem and drive change he will elaborate on his vision that everyone can be a changemaker and will explain ashoka's approach to supporting social entrepreneurs group entrepreneurship and the infrastructure that allows this sector to thrive reception to follow when thursday november 17 2011 5 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where knight management center gunn building g101 map audience faculty staff alumni friends students tags lecture reading sponsor public management program contact 650.724 7151 hochstetler_rachel gsb stanford edu admission admission is free for students staff faculty and alumni permalink http events stanford edu events 298 29837 last modified november 11 2011
